  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children Rehabilitation Centre (phase VII)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.1. Conducting meetings with project stakeholders 
1.2. Delivering sessions to help children reintegrate into the society after almost a decade of war in Afghanistan
1.3. Providing children with text books
1.4 Developing pictorial material for children
2.1. Developing curriculum for children education program 
2.2. Developing teaching and teaching aid materials for children education
2.3. Imparting training in Life Skills
3.1. Organizing meal plan for CRC children
3.2. Conducting sessions on health and hygiene practices and nutrition for target children and their parents
3.3 Organizing Parents-Teachers Meetings
3.4 Organizing medical checkups for CRC children
4.1. Preparing materials on issues affecting child&#x2019;s security, and mental, emotional, physical and social growth
4.2. Organizing interactive activities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to enhance the capacity of destitute children to develop their mental ability, daily-life management skills, orienting their behavior towards social cooperation and peace building. It will also be a means to enhance their mental ability and increase their awareness with respect to their rights, health &amp;amp; hygiene, land mines and environmental issues.</narrative>
  </description>
